    "description": "<p>You learn 2 Monk Stances from the list below.</p><p><strong>Entering & Exiting: </strong>Upon entering Combat you can choose which stance you start in, then on your turn you can spend <strong>1 SP</strong> swap to a different stance. You can end your Stance at any moment for free. You can only be in 1 Monk Stance at a time.</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.hDuhtnMBHSJCR8sE]{Bear Stance (Big Hits)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.E3qxOk2MjEzatHVi]{Bull Stance (Knockback)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.PnUZAmzpsynWIozh]{Cobra Stance (Counter)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.J7ocfmRfrQqHCwQT]{Gazelle Stance (Nimble)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.IlKYcOamQFrdIHd2]{Mantis Stance (Grapple)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.6vUqdhmUUcDlVLdt]{Mongoose Stance (Multi)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.1IailhrfZGOvAzu3]{Scorpion Stance (Quick Strike)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.geCLoSQ9Ci10SXb6]{Turtle Stance (Sturdy)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.wruRvvnRu9SbWukY]{Wolf Stance (Hit & Run)}</p>",
